opengl
intro
    is a specification
    graphics drivers provide the functions
    comes already installed

extensions:
    provides an API to interact with driver functions
    will be using glew

windowing:
    context creation:
        opengl does not specify window management
        window toolkit provides opengl context
        glew uses this context to call functions


shaders:
    shader program
    used to define how data is represented on screen
    uses GLSL(c type language)
    
    vertex:
        used to define attributes of verticies
    fragment:
        used to define color of pixels/fragments

objects:
    vertex buffer
        vertec attrib
    vertex array
    index

driver <-> glew <-> program


